    "ietf-yp-provenance:provenance" : "0oRRowNjeG1sBGdlYzIua2V5ASag9lhAKJTPi0zlejzRLmPPlMJkeYEpx6o0hRx7599v97GkggTzrW3XzBorScSkLP17f1Jq2dx4GcOuTmnqOgpXHHgkkA=="
  }
}


Output: "ietf-yp-provenance:provenance" injected inside the envelope, alongside eventTime.


**Method 3 — instance  (stored snapshot scenario)**

For when the source entry is stored as a YANG instance-data document (RFC 9195) — a timestamped snapshot saved to a datastore. The key must be exactly "ietf-yang-instance-data:instance-data-set".
{
  "ietf-yang-instance-data:instance-data-set": {
    "name": "source-traceability-snapshot",
    "timestamp": "2024-02-03T11:22:41Z",
    "content-data": {
      "ietf-green:sources": {
        "source": [
          {
            "id": "router-edge-01",
            "mechanisms": [ "cose-provenance" ],
            "location": "datacenter-madrid-01",
            "energy-metrics": {
              "power-watts": 187.4,
              "throughput-gbps": 38.2,
              "efficiency-gbps-per-watt": 0.204
            }
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  }
}


