@all Could you review please? this was one of the action items from previous WG call and also follow up on the last meeting Feb 19th:

- Rob: Suggesting adding an IANA registry of certification types and then having an IANA derived registry from that. 
- Jan: This makes sense to do, also you may still have some private certifications (e.g., Cisco might have their own).

1. seperate power state monitoring and power state control;
2. clarify that power-state-oper leaf in the monitoring part should be looked at as a whole with oper-state-admin leaf in the control part;
3. add three power states including on, off and low-power as initial input, further states  will be discussed in more details in the future.
